enhanced_by.reason: The push method modifies the stack state, which is relevant for setting up a non-empty stack before calling peek.
The create method initializes a stack with a single element, which can be used to set up a stack for peek testing.
The isEmpty method can be used to verify the state of the stack before and after calling peek, ensuring the stack remains unchanged.
The pop method also interacts with the stack's head, making it useful for asserting the state of the stack after peek.
